title: Madison advances to District softball semifinal game
text: Madison advances to District softball semifinal game Comment Posted Oct. 9, 2015 at 11:45 AM Posted Oct. 9, 2015 at 11:45 AM Payton Greiwe pitched the Madison varsity girls softball team to a 14-2 triumph over Higbee Wednesday night during first round play of the Class 1 District 10 tournament hosted at Sturgeon. The lady Panthers of Madison (8-12) met top-seed Sturgeon in Thursday’s semifinal contest. District championship game is 6 p.m. Friday. “We scored 12 runs in the first inning and we benefitted from the 14 walks issued to us by the two Higbee pitchers that were used,”said Madison softball coach Jon Link. Greiwe pitched four innings and gave up two base hits and walks, and she struck out three. Madison Thomas came in relief to pitch the fifth inning. Billie Cullom had two hits for Madison and Breanna Hancock also had a hit. Higbee finished its softball season with a record of 3-18. Moberly Monitor-Index - Moberly, MO
